d: 5874415_20249_2_0.zip (file)\r\n  deleted: 5874415_20227_2_0.zip (file)\r\n(git)-[incoming-processed] % git checkout incoming\r\nSwitched to branch 'incoming'\r\n(git)-[incoming] % datalad diff -f incoming~1 -t incoming\r\n  deleted: 5874415_20227_2_0.zip (file)\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnly the latter result is factually correct. It seems the pattern is whenever the worktree doesn't match the queries branch, results are wrong.\r\n\r\nThe reason is an inappropriate test in GitRepo._diffstatus() that uses that worktree as a reference, even when the `to` state to compare against is not None (i.e. the worktree).\r\n\r\nThis is a likely source of a range of diff failures on windows, were, due to the presence of adjusted branches, we are always diffing a branch that is not checked out when using names like `master` as the state ID.", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3997/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3